# Modern Web Dev Standards

## Stack

Next.js 15 App Router, React 19, TypeScript (strict), Tailwind CSS 4, Framer Motion, shadcn/ui.

Use `@/` path aliases. Shared logic in `lib/`, UI in `components/`.

## Server vs Client Components

- Default to Server Components
- Add `"use client"` only for hooks, event handlers, or browser APIs
- Never mark static content as client just for convenience

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
"use client";
export default function About() { return <p>Hello</p>; }

// ✅ GOOD
export default function About() { return <p>Hello</p>; }
```

## Next.js Patterns

- `next/image` for images, `next/link` for navigation, `next/font` for fonts
- Export `metadata` / `generateMetadata` from server route files
- Dynamic routes: `params` and `searchParams` are Promises in Next 15 — always await
- Lazy-load heavy client UI via `dynamic(..., { ssr: false })` in `ClientShell` or page files

## TypeScript

- Explicit props interfaces; avoid `any`
- Type-only imports: `import type { Metadata } from "next"`
- Derive types from data sources instead of duplicating shapes

## Performance

- Split below-the-fold sections and effects into separate chunks
- Set explicit image dimensions to prevent layout shift
- Prefer CSS transitions over JS for simple hover/focus states
- Do not run sync heavy work in client `useEffect` on mount

## Quality

- Run `npm run lint` and `npm run typecheck` after substantive changes
- Minimize scope — focused diffs, no unrelated refactors
